modules.description: Provides operations to construct and manipulate hierarchical keys represented as strings with slash-separated segments. Supports adding segments, extracting parent and child components, and comparing keys. Used to model file system paths or structured data keys in a normalized, immutable format.

Provides functions for reading from and writing to key/value stores, including get, set, and remove operations. Works with string-based keys and values, and supports persistent or in-memory storage backends. Used to interface with storage devices in MirageOS applications such as embedded systems or network services.

Provides operations to interact with a key-value store, including checking existence, retrieving values, partial reads, listing entries, and obtaining metadata like size, last modified time, and digest. Works with keys of type Key.t and returns results with specific error handling for value and dictionary types. Used to manage structured data stores, validate key types, and access partial or metadata information efficiently.
